content.$t:
There will be one round involved in the competition. Every team will choose their own themes and present their ramp-walk based on that theme. Their performance should be original, creative and transitions and choreography should be smooth. 
Judges will give a final decision based on their walk, presentation, body language, oratory skills, and their way of expressing themselves, confidence and presence of mind. We will give cash prizes and goodies to top two models. Prizes will be announced later.

Rules and Regulations:
1) Team size: Permitted team size is 15-22. At max 4 designers and 14 models along with maximum 4 members who handle light and sound arrangements and miscellaneous coordination and choreography.
2) You can choose your own theme.
Participating teams should carry their music on a CD or Aux.
3) Props are allowed. Lighting of candles, matches or cigarettes on stage is not allowed and will result
in disqualification of the team.
4) Music is to be submitted in CD/ pen drive. The teams are expected to label the CD or Pen drive
properly to avoid confusion and they must submit them to the organizers at least an hour before the event
starts. The team should carry at least two extra pen drives for backup.
5) The teams are required to clear the stage with the help of organizers immediately after their
performance.
6) Vulgarity of any kind will lead to disqualification. Vulgarity is strongly prohibited. Any form of obscenity will lead to debarring the team from the competition.
­Use of cigarettes, alcohol, and any unfair means is strongly prohibited.
7) A green room will be provided for changing purpose.
8) All team members have to carry the valid ID card.
Judgement criteria-
Teams will be judged on the basis of the costumes, theme originality, depiction of theme, walking stance, coordination and attitude.
Decision of the judges will be final and binding.
NSIT or the organisers will not be responsible for any damage or loss of property.
Duration of performance : ­Time limit (per team-from when your team is announced to when you get off the ramp) : 10 minutes(on stage time) + 5 minutes for choreo adjustments and transition time.

1. Team size of 5-25 people. Students who are registered in any program of an educational Institute of India and have a valid identity card can participate in the event.

3. The teams must bring their track in a pen-drive in audio format (.mp3).

4. In all cases, the judges' decision will be final and binding.

Rounds - 
I. Eliminations Round
Teams need to perform a dance sequence without any theme for the same.
Time limit: 4-7 min (+1 min setup time).

II. Semi final and Final round: (Street Dance Battle Ground) 
The shortlisted teams will then have a face-off in the battle round.
Time limit: 6-8 minutes(+1 min setup time).

content.$t: Two teams of 5 members each will compete against each other to steal their opponents’ flag or to eliminate all members of the opposing team in a field full of obstacles using rubber knives.

gs$cell.inputValue: Two teams of 5 members each will compete against each other to steal their opponents’ flag or to eliminate all members of the opposing team in a field full of obstacles using rubber knives.
gs$cell.$t: Two teams of 5 members each will compete against each other to steal their opponents’ flag or to eliminate all members of the opposing team in a field full of obstacles using rubber knives.

content.$t:
•	Each team has 5 members wearing plastic bibs and 5 knives, each team starts in their own half of the field and needs to infiltrate the other team’s half to either steal the opponent’s flag or eliminate all members of the opposing team within 10 minutes.
•	Event format will be of a knock-out tournament type.
•	Match takes 11 minutes:
   o	1 minute for the teams to hide their flags in their area
   o	10 minutes to capture the flag or eliminate the team.
•	Elimination takes place when one person strikes an opponent with a rubber knife covered in the team’s color powder. Eliminations will be judged from the color marks left on the bibs.
•	Members are allowed to use knives of their teammates, but not of their opponents [distinguishable by color powder or by the tape marks on the handles]
•	Direct physical contact of more than 5 seconds is illegal, will result in elimination of the player. Second such offense results in team disqualification.
•	In the case of time limit getting over with neither team successful in stealing the flag or eliminating the team, the team with most remaining members on the field wins.
•	Stepping out of bounds results in a warning, second time results in member disqualification.

content.$t:
Folk Dance is not just reminiscence of the past, but it acts as a passage in connecting our past and future. 

Enriching our very origin and roots, it leads the road all the way back to the diverse cultures, and the vast multitude of ethnicity, of which we are a part. 

Paying a glorious tribute to all our beautiful dance forms, Capella-The Choreography Society Of NSUT, under the aegis of Moksha, NSUT Delhi presents, ‘Kalakriti, The folk dance competition’, bringing together, a celebration by the graceful dancers, of our inherent traditions and diversity.

Come be a part, both in witnessing and creating dances that mesmerize our souls and enriches our age-old heritage!

content.$t:
Kalakriti

 Rules and regulations

1.	There is a maximum team limit of 20 for the event, non-performing included. Cross-college teams are NOT allowed.

2.	The total time allowed to each team ‘on stage’ is 10 minutes (including introduction, setup and other miscellaneous activities).

3.	(a) The Organizing Committee shall not provide any instruments/accompanists. The contestants should install/ test their tracks with the equipment available at the venue beforehand. No extra time shall be given during the time of the performance.

           (b) The teams should bring their music tracks in the form of pen
                 drives.

           (c) Teams need to specify beforehand, if they will be using any kind of props. The organizers will not be providing props (including chairs or stools)

4.	In case the participants exceed the time limit, the judges will be free to disqualify the participating team.

5.	The Organizing Committee reserves the right to change the venue, the time and rules, if need be.
6. All teams to mail their track to capella.nsut@gmail.com before 18th March, and additionally carry it in a pen drive

7. The decision of Judges will be final and binding.

content.$t:
Ever look up at the stars and wonder what it would be like to see them up close? We haven't invented interstellar travel yet, so we'll have to make do with the next best thing.

Nakshatra NSUT is back with their premier star gazing event - Night's Watch! Join us as we gather around to observe the beauty of the stars, the might of planets, reminiscent of the golden age of sky gazing. We'll set up the telescope and observe a number of celestial bodies, which may include planets like Mars and Saturn and stars such as Sirius and Vega and much more!

Be sure to be a part of this phenomenon!
